## 7. Responsive Design

### 7.1 Breakpoint Strategy

```css
Mobile First Approach

Base (0px): Mobile portrait
└→ Single column layouts
└→ Full-width elements
└→ Stacked navigation
└→ Bottom sheet modals

sm (640px): Mobile landscape, small tablets
└→ 2-column cards grid
└→ Horizontal form layouts
└→ Side-by-side buttons

md (768px): Tablet portrait
└→ Sidebar layouts appear
└→ 3-column grids
└→ Table becomes scrollable (not stacked)

lg (1024px): Tablet landscape, small desktops
└→ Full desktop layouts
└→ 4-column grids
└→ All features visible

xl (1280px): Desktop
└→ Max content width enforced
└→ Optimal spacing

2xl (1536px): Large desktop
└→ Same as xl (no changes)
```

### 7.2 Component Adaptations

#### **Navigation**

```
Mobile (< 768px):
└→ Hamburger menu (top left)
└→ Slide-out drawer navigation
└→ Full-screen overlay

Tablet/Desktop (>= 768px):
└→ Top navigation bar
└→ All items visible
└→ Dropdowns for sub-items
```

#### **Tables**

```
Mobile (< 768px):
└→ Horizontal scroll
└→ Fixed first column (supplier name)
└→ Swipe indicator

Desktop (>= 768px):
└→ Full table visible
└→ All columns shown
└→ Hover actions appear
```

#### **Forms**

```
Mobile:
└→ Single column
└→ Full-width inputs
└→ Stacked buttons

Tablet+:
└→ 2-column for short fields
└→ Side-by-side related fields
└→ Inline buttons (right-aligned)
```

#### **Dashboards**

```
Mobile:
└→ KPI cards: 1 column
└→ Charts: 1 column, vertical scroll
└→ Touch-friendly chart interactions

Tablet:
└→ KPI cards: 2 columns
└→ Charts: 2 columns
└→ Larger touch targets

Desktop:
└→ KPI cards: 4 columns
└→ Charts: 2-3 columns grid
└→ Hover interactions
```

### 7.3 Touch Targets

**Minimum touch target size:**

- Buttons: 44x44px (iOS HIG)
- Icons: 40x40px clickable area
- Links: 32px min height with padding
- Table rows: 56px min height

**Spacing between touch targets:**

- Minimum 8px gap between interactive elements
- 16px preferred for better usability

