## 8. Accessibility

### 8.1 WCAG 2.1 Level AA Compliance

#### **Color Contrast**

**Text Contrast Ratios:**

- Normal text (16px+): 4.5:1 minimum
- Large text (24px+): 3:1 minimum
- UI components: 3:1 minimum

**Verified Combinations:**

- slate-900 on white: 19.4:1 ✓
- slate-700 on white: 12.6:1 ✓
- slate-600 on white: 7.9:1 ✓
- primary-600 on white: 8.6:1 ✓
- error-600 on white: 9.1:1 ✓

#### **Keyboard Navigation**

**All interactive elements accessible via keyboard:**

- Tab order follows visual order
- Skip to main content link (first tab)
- Focus visible on all elements
- No keyboard traps

**Custom Keyboard Shortcuts:**

- All shortcuts include modifier key (Cmd/Ctrl)
- Shortcuts documented in help menu
- Can be disabled in settings

#### **Screen Reader Support**

**ARIA Labels:**

```tsx
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <X className="w-4 h-4" />
</button>

<input
  type="text"
  aria-label="Search suppliers"
  aria-describedby="search-help"
/>
<span id="search-help" className="sr-only">
  Search by name, code, or contact
</span>

<div role="alert" aria-live="polite">
  Supplier saved successfully
</div>
```

**Form Validation:**

```tsx
<input
  aria-invalid={error ? "true" : "false"}
  aria-describedby={error ? "email-error" : undefined}
/>;
{
  error && (
    <p id="email-error" role="alert">
      {error}
    </p>
  );
}
```

**Dynamic Content:**

```tsx
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  {results.length} results found
</div>
```

#### **Focus Management**

- Modal opens → Focus moves to first interactive element
- Modal closes → Focus returns to trigger
- Form submission error → Focus moves to first error
- Page load → Focus on main heading (h1)

#### **Alternative Text**

All images must have alt text:

```tsx
<img src="chart.png" alt="Performance trend showing 10% improvement" />

<!-- Decorative images -->
<img src="decoration.svg" alt="" role="presentation" />
```

### 8.2 Accessibility Checklist

**Every Feature Must:**

- [ ] Be keyboard accessible
- [ ] Have visible focus indicators
- [ ] Include ARIA labels where needed
- [ ] Support screen readers
- [ ] Meet color contrast requirements
- [ ] Have adequate touch targets (mobile)
- [ ] Announce dynamic content changes
- [ ] Handle errors accessibly

